So they're selling
to people who cycle.

00:30:31.400 --> 00:30:35.280
And in the male brigade, that
involves wearing funny clothes

00:30:35.280 --> 00:30:38.030
and shaving your legs
and, in some cases,

00:30:38.030 --> 00:30:39.990
forgetting to get the
six-pack before you

00:30:39.990 --> 00:30:42.740
put the funny clothes on, which
makes the whole thing less

00:30:42.740 --> 00:30:45.258
delightful on the eye.

00:30:45.258 --> 00:30:49.430
But then if you look at
countries where people cycle,

00:30:49.430 --> 00:30:50.950
they're not cyclists.

00:30:50.950 --> 00:30:52.640
They're just normal people.

00:30:52.640 --> 00:30:55.380
They just get on
a bike and pedal.

00:30:55.380 --> 00:30:57.780
They don't have
to do weird stuff.

00:30:57.780 --> 00:31:02.520
So we are trying to
make cycling normal.

00:31:02.520 --> 00:31:05.030
And lots of people,
nearly everybody,

00:31:05.030 --> 00:31:06.900
learned to ride a bike.

00:31:06.900 --> 00:31:08.900
And that sense of
freedom and simplicity

00:31:08.900 --> 00:31:11.350
you get with riding a
bike is so delightful.

00:31:11.350 --> 00:31:13.320
It never leaves you.

00:31:13.320 --> 00:31:15.285
So we created basically
a bike dispenser.

00:31:15.285 --> 00:31:17.360
That's our Brompton Dock.

00:31:17.360 --> 00:31:20.870
We have 50 of those in
24 cities across the UK.

00:31:20.870 --> 00:31:23.997
Use a smartphone, you walk
up, you type in a code,

00:31:23.997 --> 00:31:25.830
the door pips open out,
out comes a Brompton

00:31:25.830 --> 00:31:26.920
and off you go.

00:31:26.920 --> 00:31:30.127
Average hire is 4 and 1/2 days.

00:31:30.127 --> 00:31:31.210
So you don't take it back.

00:31:31.210 --> 00:31:31.790
You can take it anywhere.

00:31:31.790 --> 00:31:33.748
You can take it to France,
you can take it over

00:31:33.748 --> 00:31:34.620
to US for a week.

00:31:34.620 --> 00:31:36.620
It's 2 pounds 50 a day.

00:31:36.620 --> 00:31:38.800
And you can drop it
back whenever you like.

00:31:38.800 --> 00:31:40.600
That should be
outside your building,

00:31:40.600 --> 00:31:42.634
and it should have
these inside it

00:31:42.634 --> 00:31:44.300
so your staff can go
wherever they like.

00:31:44.300 --> 00:31:46.930
It's a no-flipping-brainer.

00:31:46.930 --> 00:31:50.384
And it means that somebody who
is a cyclist has a bicycle,

00:31:50.384 --> 00:31:51.550
and they're going somewhere.

00:31:51.550 --> 00:31:53.900
They'll just say, we'll
go take one of the bikes.

00:31:53.900 --> 00:31:54.930
Let's go.

00:31:54.930 --> 00:31:55.540
Hop on a bike.

00:31:55.540 --> 00:31:57.331
Whiz off, fold it up,
no trouble at all.

00:31:57.331 --> 00:31:58.956
Someone's at the
weekend again, they're

00:31:58.956 --> 00:32:00.660
going with their children
or they're going on holiday.

00:32:00.660 --> 00:32:03.090
Take two bikes, go with
your children and have fun.

00:32:03.090 --> 00:32:04.580
No-brainer.

00:32:04.580 --> 00:32:07.570
Cycling needs a catalyst
to get more people cycling.

00:32:07.570 --> 00:32:08.842
You can't just rely on people.

00:32:08.842 --> 00:32:11.175
You've got to give them a
really little barrier to entry

00:32:11.175 --> 00:32:12.231
and let them try it.

00:32:12.231 --> 00:32:14.480
Once you try it, you love
it, but you haven't tried it

00:32:14.480 --> 00:32:16.195
for so long because it
suddenly became uncool,

00:32:16.195 --> 00:32:17.940
and you've got to drive
a car because then you've

00:32:17.940 --> 00:32:20.481
got loads of money and you're
going to get the chicks and all

00:32:20.481 --> 00:32:21.140
that stuff.

00:32:21.140 --> 00:32:24.070
But actually, that's just nuts,
and the bike is super cool,

00:32:24.070 --> 00:32:26.970
but you've just
forgotten about it.

00:32:26.970 --> 00:32:27.920
It's quite innovative.

