00:38:56.003 --> 00:38:56.919
WILL BUTLER-ADAMS: IP.

00:38:56.919 --> 00:39:01.110
So in our world-- bike
world-- most people

00:39:01.110 --> 00:39:02.252
just assemble bikes.

00:39:02.252 --> 00:39:04.210
Actually, most people
don't even assemble them,

00:39:04.210 --> 00:39:06.480
but those that do make
them assemble them.

00:39:06.480 --> 00:39:07.460
Assembling is easy.

00:39:07.460 --> 00:39:10.160
The value in a bike-- anyway,
in my opinion-- is the frame.

00:39:10.160 --> 00:39:12.200
That's the clever bit.

00:39:12.200 --> 00:39:15.020
And the way we make
our frame is weird.

00:39:15.020 --> 00:39:16.450
It's anal.

00:39:16.450 --> 00:39:18.780
It has a tolerance of about
plus or minus 0.2 of a mil

00:39:18.780 --> 00:39:20.740
versus a normal bike
plus or minus 2 mil.

00:39:20.740 --> 00:39:22.190
We use CMM machines.

00:39:22.190 --> 00:39:23.080
We braze it.

00:39:23.080 --> 00:39:24.970
We do weird stuff,
because it demands it,

00:39:24.970 --> 00:39:27.136
because it's already a
compromise, because it folds.

00:39:27.136 --> 00:39:29.650
So everything else must
not be a compromise.

00:39:29.650 --> 00:39:33.300
There is far more IP in
the manufacturing process

00:39:33.300 --> 00:39:34.710
than there is in the product.

00:39:34.710 --> 00:39:36.579
So we have a 200-grand
auto-braze machine.

00:39:36.579 --> 00:39:37.870
It's got thermographic cameras.

00:39:37.870 --> 00:39:38.960
It's PRC controlled.

00:39:38.960 --> 00:39:41.280
Its hydraulic system is
designed and made in house.

00:39:41.280 --> 00:39:43.410
We've got oodles of weird stuff.

00:39:43.410 --> 00:39:46.812
So if we got someone
else to make it,

00:39:46.812 --> 00:39:48.270
we'd have to teach
them how to make

00:39:48.270 --> 00:39:50.050
the machines to make the bike.

00:39:50.050 --> 00:39:52.633
And we have to teach them how
to maintain the machines and all

00:39:52.633 --> 00:39:53.590
the proactive stuff.

00:39:53.590 --> 00:39:55.142
And therefore, that's fine.

00:39:55.142 --> 00:39:55.850
They could do it.

00:39:55.850 --> 00:39:56.850
Anyone can do it.

00:39:56.850 --> 00:39:58.891
It's not that difficult.
We'd have to teach them.

00:39:58.891 --> 00:40:00.320
It would take three
or four years.

00:40:00.320 --> 00:40:02.778
So if that happened and we went
to the most sensible place,

00:40:02.778 --> 00:40:05.012
which would be
Taichung in Taiwan,

00:40:05.012 --> 00:40:07.470
where most of the good-quality
bikes in the world are made,

00:40:07.470 --> 00:40:09.450
someone could work
for us for five years,

00:40:09.450 --> 00:40:11.085
understand our
process, then they

00:40:11.085 --> 00:40:13.210
could work for a competitor
and not even move house

00:40:13.210 --> 00:40:14.751
or take their children
out of school.

00:40:14.751 --> 00:40:16.700
That just means that
your knowledge just

00:40:16.700 --> 00:40:19.410
seeps out of the business
to the competition.

00:40:19.410 --> 00:40:22.900
We are the only bonkers
people making bikes in London.

00:40:22.900 --> 00:40:26.030
So therefore our
knowledge is quite safe

00:40:26.030 --> 00:40:28.580
unless our staff decide they
want to emigrate to Asia.

00:40:28.580 --> 00:40:31.110
So actually being
manufactured in London

00:40:31.110 --> 00:40:32.730
wasn't a conscious
decision, but it

00:40:32.730 --> 00:40:34.610
has been an important
part in protecting

00:40:34.610 --> 00:40:35.970
our intellectual property.

00:40:35.970 --> 00:40:38.230
People think bikes are simple.

00:40:38.230 --> 00:40:41.800
They are to a point because,
remember, someone rides this.

00:40:41.800 --> 00:40:44.390
You will ride your bike
for the next 15 years

00:40:44.390 --> 00:40:46.600
every day, potentially.

00:40:46.600 --> 00:40:47.935
What happens if it breaks?

00:40:47.935 --> 00:40:49.390
You're next to a bus.

00:40:49.390 --> 00:40:51.200
That is not a funny outcome.

00:40:51.200 --> 00:40:54.510
So the implications of
getting the quality right

00:40:54.510 --> 00:40:59.040
and having a product that's
robust is really important.

00:40:59.040 --> 00:41:01.780
And so you can make
something look like this but,

00:41:01.780 --> 00:41:04.390
personally, I would be
wary about jumping on it.

00:41:04.390 --> 00:41:06.390
It might be fine for
the first six months,

00:41:06.390 --> 00:41:08.556
but you're whizzing down a
hill and the thing snaps,

00:41:08.556 --> 00:41:10.672
it's an unfunny outcome.

